## C++
0. prerequisite 
- install crypto++ package

1. make clean && make
2.  ./sign_verify

- if you need to debug some feature in this code, you should set TEST to 1 in the source code (replace 0 to 1)
#define TEST 0 



## Python 
0. prerequisite
$ pip install cryptography
$ pip install pyopenssl

1. execute a client 

$ python 1_keygen.py   # generate two files (alice.pub, alice.pem)

$ python 2_sign.py  # sign a message and generate a signature

$ python 23_verify.py # verify the message by the signature (given)
